{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:19.544375+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer: **pnpm is required; npm is NOT acceptable**\n\nThere are multiple layers of enforcement in this repository that make pnpm the only permitted package manager. Here is the evidence:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `package.json` — `\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"` (Corepack field)\nThe `packageManager` field is a standard mechanism recognized by [Node.js Corepack](https://nodejs.org/api/corepack.html). When present, Corepack will ensure that only the specified package manager (pnpm 10.20.0) is used. If you try to run `npm` or `yarn` in a Corepack-enabled environment, it will either block you or warn you.\n\n### 2. `package.json` — `\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"` (Hard gate)\nThis is the most explicit and forceful guard. The `only-allow` package checks which package manager is being used and **exits with an error** if it is not `pnpm`. This means:\n- Running `npm install` will **fail immediately** with an error message.\n- Running `yarn install` will also fail.\n- Only `pnpm install` will succeed.\n\n### 3. Lock file: `pnpm-lock.yaml` (no `package-lock.json`)\nThe repository ships a `pnpm-lock.yaml` lock file and does **not** include a `package-lock.json` (npm's lock file). Using npm would generate a different lock file, leading to inconsistent dependency resolutions and potential merge conflicts.\n\n### 4. CI/CD: `.github/workflows/release.yml` uses pnpm exclusively\nThe release workflow explicitly:\n- Uses `pnpm/action-setup@v4` to install pnpm.\n- Runs all commands (`pnpm install`, `pnpm run lint-fix`, `pnpm run test:unit`, `pnpm run build`) via pnpm.\n\n### 5. README: All documented commands use `pnpm`\nThe README instructs contributors to use pnpm for every operation (`pnpm install`, `pnpm run dev`, `pnpm run build`, `pnpm run test:unit`, `pnpm run lint`). *(Note: there is one minor inconsistency where `npm run lint-fix` appears in the README instead of `pnpm run lint-fix`, but this is likely a typo given all other evidence.)*\n\n### 6. `.gitignore` includes `pnpm-debug.log*`\nThe `.gitignore` file logs pnpm-specific debug files, further confirming pnpm as the intended toolchain.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Signal | Where | Effect |\n|---|---|---|\n| `packageManager: \"pnpm@10.20.0\"` | `package.json` | Corepack enforces pnpm |\n| `preinstall: \"npx only-allow pnpm\"` | `package.json` | **Hard block** — npm/yarn fail at install time |\n| `pnpm-lock.yaml` (no `package-lock.json`) | repo root | Lock file mismatch if npm is used |\n| `pnpm/action-setup@v4` | CI workflow | CI runs pnpm only |\n| All README commands | `README.md` | Documentation directs pnpm |\n\n**Conclusion:** Contributors are expected to use **pnpm (version 10.20.0)**. Using npm is **not acceptable** — it will be actively blocked by the `preinstall` script and is incompatible with the project's lock file, CI pipeline, and Corepack configuration.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 764, "prompt_tokens": 12359, "total_tokens": 13123, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 17, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 11008, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0012919938, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0006273138, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00066468}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863185-x6h8uHzcT4cj7nJPsAUN", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b7-b240-76b0-974d-d3b6422d0d1d-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12359, "output_tokens": 764, "total_tok